/-! ### AM4: removable singularity ÔÇö pole unit is analytic at `1` -/

/-- The pole unit `riemannZetaPoleUnit` is analytic at `1`.

Proof: `(z - 1) * ╬Â(z)` is bounded near `1` (by `riemannZeta_residue_one`),
