-- Mellin transform of a real-valued function. The keystone is:
--
--   `mellin_star_ofReal : ÔêÇ (f : ÔäØ ÔåÆ ÔäØ) (s : Ôäé),
--      mellin (fun t => (f t : Ôäé)) (star s)
--        = star (mellin (fun t => (f t : Ôäé)) s)`.
--
-- Once this lemma lands, it propagates up the FE-pair definition chain
-- (`completedHurwitzZetaEvenÔéÇ 0 = (hurwitzEvenFEPair 0).╬øÔéÇ (s/2) / 2`,
--  whose underlying kernel `evenKernel` is `ÔäØ ÔåÆ ÔäØ`) to a Schwarz
-- symmetry on `completedRiemannZetaÔéÇ`, then on `entireRiemannXi`.
--
-- This section proves the keystone. The FE-pair lift and final
