/-- Ô¡É **PROVED ÔÇö Mellin transform of an `ÔäØ ÔåÆ Ôäé`-lifted real function
commutes with conjugation.** For any real-valued `f : ÔäØ ÔåÆ ÔäØ`,
`mellin (ofReal Ôêÿ f) (star s) = star (mellin (ofReal Ôêÿ f) s)`.

Proof: pull `star` (= complex conjugation) outside the integral via
`MeasureTheory.integral_conj`, then verify the per-point identity
`(t : Ôäé) ^ (star s ÔêÆ 1) ÔÇó (f t : Ôäé) = conj((t : Ôäé) ^ (s ÔêÆ 1) ÔÇó (f t : Ôäé))`
on `t Ôêê Ioi 0` using:
* `Complex.cpow_conj` (with `(t : Ôäé).arg = 0 Ôëá ¤Ç` for `t > 0`),
* `Complex.conj_ofReal` (for the real `f t`),
* `Complex.star_def` (`star = conj` on `Ôäé`).

