/-- **Closed-form error bound discharged on the finite band.**
The IBP/Stieltjes-side hypothesis: there's an `error : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé` whose
imaginary part is bounded by the slab-specific closed form on all of
`[10, 140]`. -/
def closedFormErrorControlledOnFiniteBand (error : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé) : Prop :=
  ÔêÇ {z : Ôäé} {T : ÔäØ},
    10 Ôëñ T ÔåÆ T Ôëñ 140 ÔåÆ
    0 < z.im ÔåÆ
    2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) Ôëñ T ÔåÆ
      |(error z).im|
        Ôëñ closedFormSErrorBoundCD (slabCD T).1 (slabCD T).2 z.im T

/-- ­ƒîƒ **PROVED ÔÇö Finite-band error margin** via `slabCD`. Direct `le_trans`
chaining the IBP-side error bound with the slab-side model-margin
domination ÔÇö BOTH using the same `(slabCD T).1, (slabCD T).2`. -/
theorem finiteBand_errorMargin_of_slabCD
    {M : CloudDensityTailModelDecomposition}
    {error : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé}
    (hzeros : M.zeros = zeros100ceil)
    (herr : closedFormErrorControlledOnFiniteBand error)
    {z : Ôäé} {T : ÔäØ}
    (hT10 : 10 Ôëñ T) (hT140 : T Ôëñ 140)
    (hy : 0 < z.im) (hreg : 2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) Ôëñ T) :
    |(error z).im| Ôëñ -(M.model z).im :=
  le_trans (herr hT10 hT140 hy hreg)
    (hclosed_on_10_140_zeros100ceil_slabCD M hzeros hT10 hT140 hy hreg)

