/-- ­ƒôª **`TrueKernelTailData`** ÔÇö packaged xi-tail data for the true
rational complex kernel. Carries everything
`adaptiveComplexTailIBPBoundData_trueKernel` needs beyond a real-IBP
family witness:

* `conv` ÔÇö adaptive complex tail convergence for the true kernel;
* `true_int` / `wrap_int` ÔÇö interval integrability of `kernel ┬À S` on
  every finite window in the adaptive band (true and wrapper kernel);
* `error_im_eq_tail_im` ÔÇö the xi residual error's imaginary part
  equals the imaginary part of the true tail at every `(z, T)` in the
  adaptive band.

This is a `Type` (not `Prop`) because `conv` carries the data field
`tail : ÔäØ ÔåÆ Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé`. -/
structure TrueKernelTailData
    (S : ÔäØ ÔåÆ ÔäØ) (R : RealIBPFamilyData S) (error : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé) where
  /-- Adaptive complex tail convergence for the true rational kernel. -/
  conv : AdaptiveComplexDensityTailFamilyConverges
            pairedCauchyComplexKernelTrue S
  /-- True-kernel finite-window interval integrability. -/
  true_int :
    ÔêÇ {z : Ôäé} {T X : ÔäØ},
      10 Ôëñ T ÔåÆ T Ôëñ 140 ÔåÆ 0 < z.im ÔåÆ
      2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) Ôëñ T ÔåÆ
      IntervalIntegrable
        (fun u => pairedCauchyComplexKernelTrue u z * (S u : Ôäé))
        MeasureTheory.volume T X
  /-- Wrapper-kernel finite-window interval integrability. -/
  wrap_int :
    ÔêÇ {z : Ôäé} {T X : ÔäØ},
      10 Ôëñ T ÔåÆ T Ôëñ 140 ÔåÆ 0 < z.im ÔåÆ
      2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) Ôëñ T ÔåÆ
      IntervalIntegrable
        (fun u => pairedCauchyComplexKernelDeriv u z * (S u : Ôäé))
        MeasureTheory.volume T X
  /-- The xi residual error's imaginary part equals the true tail's. -/
  error_im_eq_tail_im :
    ÔêÇ {z : Ôäé} {T : ÔäØ},
      10 Ôëñ T ÔåÆ T Ôëñ 140 ÔåÆ 0 < z.im ÔåÆ
      2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) Ôëñ T ÔåÆ
      (error z).im = (conv.tail T z).im

/-- ­ƒîƒ­ƒîƒ­ƒîƒ **PROVED ÔÇö `AdaptiveComplexTailIBPBoundData` from
`TrueKernelTailData`.** Pure assembly: routes the four
`TrueKernelTailData` fields through the ┬ºCCXX
`adaptiveComplexTailIBPBoundData_trueKernel`. -/
theorem adaptiveComplexTailIBPBoundData_of_trueKernelTailData
    (S : ÔäØ ÔåÆ ÔäØ) (R : RealIBPFamilyData S) (error : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé)
    (D : TrueKernelTailData S R error) :
    AdaptiveComplexTailIBPBoundData
      pairedCauchyComplexKernelTrue S D.conv error :=
  adaptiveComplexTailIBPBoundData_trueKernel
    S R D.conv error D.error_im_eq_tail_im D.true_int D.wrap_int

/-- ­ƒîƒ­ƒîƒ­ƒîƒ­ƒîƒ **PROVED ÔÇö `ActualDensityTailData` from `TrueKernelTailData`.**
The final true-kernel constructor: takes the standard model fields
+ xi log-derivative decomposition + `TrueKernelTailData`, produces
an `ActualDensityTailData`. The `hbound` field is discharged via the
adaptive-bound machine. -/
noncomputable def actualDensityTailData_of_trueKernelTailData
    (S : ÔäØ ÔåÆ ÔäØ) (R : RealIBPFamilyData S)
    (M : CloudDensityTailModelDecomposition)
    (hM_zeros : M.zeros = zeros100ceil)
    (hmodelAnti : AntiHerglotzUHP M.model)
    (error : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé)
    (hdecomp : ÔêÇ z : Ôäé,
        (Ôêâ T : ÔäØ, 10 Ôëñ T Ôêº T Ôëñ 140 Ôêº
          2 * (1 + |z.re| + z.im) Ôëñ T) ÔåÆ
        logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z = M.model z + error z)
    (D : TrueKernelTailData S R error) :
