-- The residual route from ┬ºCCLVIIÔÇô┬ºCCLXXX assumes its analytic hypotheses
-- pointwise at every UHP `z` in the relevant band, with no guard against
-- hypothetical zeros of `XiPullback`. Lean's `a / 0 = 0` totalization
-- then forces `xiResidualError M ¤ü = ÔêÆM.model ¤ü` at any such zero, making
-- residual-equality / strict-bound hypotheses unprovable except by first
-- ruling out the zero (which is RH). The fix mirrors ┬º6-bis / ┬ºCCL-bis:
-- weaken the public analytic input by an explicit `XiPullback z Ôëá 0`
