-- ┬ºCCXCVI. Log-derivative decomposition bridges for tail-limit inputs
-- =====================================================================
-- The two tail-limit identities (`Hhigh : XiHighResidualAsTailLimit`
-- and `Hmid : XiCanonicalResidualAsTailLimit`) both have the shape
--   `Tendsto (true-kernel partials) atTop (­ØôØ (xiResidualError M z))`.
-- The "residual" target is opaque. The standard explicit-formula form is
--   `logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z = M.model z + L`
-- where `L` is the tail limit of the true-kernel partials. Since
--   `xiResidualError M z = logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z ÔêÆ M.model z`
-- by definition, the two shapes are equivalent. This section provides
-- bridges that convert the explicit-formula shape into the tail-limit
-- shape.

/-- ­ƒîƒ **PROVED ÔÇö `XiHighResidualAsTailLimit` from a log-derivative
decomposition.** -/
