-- ┬ºCCCXVI. ╬¥-side Hadamard source + bridge through chain rule
-- =====================================================================
-- The Hadamard product theorem is naturally stated for the completed
-- ╬¥ on the s-plane. The chain rule `XiPullback_logDeriv_chain_rule`
-- converts to the z-plane pullback. This section adds the ╬¥-side
-- source Prop and bridges it to `XiHadamardLogDerivativeSourceAFZ`.
--
-- Note on differentiability: `completedXiFunction` (╬ô-based) is NOT
-- automatically differentiable at every `1/2 + I┬Àz` with `0 < z.im`
-- ÔÇö ╬ô has poles at non-positive integers and the trivial-zero
-- cancellation isn't built into the definition. The ╬¥-side source
-- carries differentiability AFZ as a field; concrete inhabitants
-- discharge it via the Hadamard product factorization or by
-- bridging to Mathlib's `entireRiemannXi`.

/-- ­ƒôª **`CompletedXiLogDerivativeSourceAFZ`** ÔÇö ╬¥-side Hadamard source
on the s-plane. -/
structure CompletedXiLogDerivativeSourceAFZ : Type where
  xiZeroContribution : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé
  xi_diff_at :
    ÔêÇ s : Ôäé,
      completedXiFunction s Ôëá 0 ÔåÆ
      DifferentiableAt Ôäé completedXiFunction s
  xi_logDeriv_eq :
    ÔêÇ s : Ôäé,
      completedXiFunction s Ôëá 0 ÔåÆ
      logDerivativeResponse completedXiFunction s = xiZeroContribution s

/-- **Pullback of the ╬¥-side zero contribution to the z-plane.**
`╬ø[╬×] = I ┬À ╬ø[╬¥](┬¢ + I┬Àz)` from the chain rule. -/
noncomputable def pullbackZeroContribution
    (H : CompletedXiLogDerivativeSourceAFZ) : Ôäé ÔåÆ Ôäé :=
  fun z => Complex.I * H.xiZeroContribution ((1 / 2 : Ôäé) + Complex.I * z)

