-- ┬ºCCCLXXX. Subtype zero index candidate + zero-at-origin hazard audit
-- =====================================================================
-- A natural candidate for `╬╣` is the subtype of nonzero zeros of
-- `completedXiFunction`. **Hazard**: the ╬ô-based `completedXiFunction`
-- definition gives `completedXiFunction 0 = 0` because of the
-- `(1/2)┬Às┬À(s-1)` polynomial prefactor in the definition. So the
-- subtype excluding 0 cannot satisfy the strong `all_completedXi_zeros`
-- field of `ConcreteCompletedXiZeroSystem` ÔÇö the zero at the origin
-- is missed.
--
-- The fix (┬ºCCCLXXXI) is `ConcreteCompletedXiNonzeroZeroSystem` whose
-- surjectivity is restricted to **nonzero** zeros, with a bridge to
-- the strong version (┬ºCCCLXXXII) under `completedXiFunction 0 Ôëá 0`.

/-- **Subtype of nonzero zeros of `completedXiFunction`.** Natural
candidate for `╬╣`. -/
def CompletedXiNonzeroZeroIndex : Type :=
  { s : Ôäé // completedXiFunction s = 0 Ôêº s Ôëá 0 }

/-- The subtype's zero-location map. -/
def completedXiNonzeroZeroLoc (i : CompletedXiNonzeroZeroIndex) : Ôäé := i.1

-- =====================================================================
-- ┬ºCCCLXXXI. Nonzero zero-system (sharper)
-- =====================================================================

/-- ­ƒôª **`ConcreteCompletedXiNonzeroZeroSystem`** ÔÇö like
`ConcreteCompletedXiZeroSystem` but the surjectivity field only
covers **nonzero** zeros. Avoids the zero-at-origin hazard. -/
